original: Blomquist, Torsten Martin, byggnadschef, Finspång, f. 7/12/11 i Mariefred av rådman Georg B. o. Lydia Hellström. — Ing:ex. v. Örebro tekn. gymn. 32. Bitr. ing. v. stadsing :kont. i Strängnäs 33-38, kommunaling. i Risinge s:n o. Finspångs samhälle 38-43, byggn :chef i Finspång sed. 43. Byggn :konsul. hos byggn :ndn i Finspång 41-44, v. ordf. i hyresndn i Finspång sed. 42, sekr. i styr. f. Finspångs Hotell A-B sed. 45.
translated: Blomquist, Torsten Martin, construction manager, Finspång, born December 7, 1911 in Mariefred to councilman Georg B. and Lydia Hellström. - Graduated from Örebro technical gymnasium in 1932. Assistant engineer at the city engineering office in Strängnäs from 1933-1938. Worked in municipal engineering in Risinge parish and Finspång community from 1938-1943. Became construction manager in Finspång in 1943. Served as building consultant to the building board in Finspång from 1941-1944, served as vice chairman of the rental board in Finspång from 1942, and held the position of secretary in the board of directors for Finspångs Hotel A-B from 1945.
